decisionBoundary <- function(svm){
    w <- colSums(coef(svm)[[1]] * ex6data1[unlist(alphaindex(svm)), 2:1])
    b <- b(svm)
    C <- param(svm)[[1]]
    return(list(slope = -w[2]/w[1], intcpt = b/w[1], C = C))
}
bound1 <- decisionBoundary(linSvm1)
g2 <- g1 + geom_abline(intercept = bound1$intcpt, slope = bound1$slope, color = 2)
g2

linSvm2 <- ksvm(V3 ~ V2 + V1,
                data = ex6data1,
                C = 100,
                type = "C-svc",
                kernel = "vanilladot", 
                kpar = list(),
                scaled = F)

bound2 <- decisionBoundary(linSvm2)
g3 <- g2 + geom_abline(intercept = bound2$intcpt, slope = bound2$slope, color = 3)
g3

1.2 SVM with Gaussian Kernels

1.2.1 Gaussian Kernel

gkGenerator <- function (sigma = 1) {
    gk <- function(Xi, Xj = NULL) {
        normSquared <- sum((Xi - Xj) ^ 2)
        # I'm not sure this needs to be coerced to a matrix, but rbfdot returns
        # a 1x1 matrix, so when in Rome...
        return(as.matrix(exp(-normSquared / (2 * sigma ^ 2))))
    }
    return(new("rbfkernel", .Data = gk, kpar = list(sigma = sigma)))
}

Because the built-in Gaussian kernel function in kernlab takes a different sigma parameter, Ive defined a function that will make it comparable to the way its calculated in the assignment.

sigTransform <- function(sigma){
    1 / (2 * sigma ^ 2)
}
x1 <- c(1, 2, 1)
x2 = c(0, 4, -1)
sigma = 2
gk <- gkGenerator(sigma)
gk(x1, x2)
##           [,1]
## [1,] 0.3246525
rbf <- rbfdot(sigTransform(sigma))
rbf(x1, x2)
##           [,1]
## [1,] 0.3246525

This should be about 0.324652. For good measure, I also checked the value using the rbfdot function built into kernlab.

Test all combination of c and sigma for the values 0.01, 0.03, 0.1, 0.3, 1, 3, 10, 30.

testParams <- function(train, val, Cs, sigs){
    paramPerformance <- data.frame()
    for(C in Cs){
        for(sig in sigs){
            svm <- ksvm(V3 ~ .,
                           data = train,
                           C = C,
                           type = "C-svc",
                           kernel = gkGenerator,
                           kpar = list(sigma = sigTransform(sig)))
            pred <- predict(svm, val[, 1:ncol(val) - 1])
            valError <- sum(pred != val[, ncol(val)]) / length(pred)
            paramPerformance <- rbind(paramPerformance,
                                      c(C, sig, error(svm), valError))
        }
    }
    colnames(paramPerformance) <- c("C", "sigma", "train.error", "val.error")
    return(paramPerformance)
}
v <- c(0.01, 0.03, 0.1, 0.3, 1, 3, 10, 30)
params3 <- testParams(ex6data3_train, ex6data3_val, v, v)
min.val.error <- params3[which.min(params3$val.error),]
svm3 <- ksvm(V3 ~ V2 + V1,
             data = ex6data3_train,
             C = min.val.error$C,
             type = "C-svc",
             kernel = gkGenerator,
             kpar = list(sigma = sigTransform(min.val.error$sigma)))
plot(svm3, data = as.data.frame(ex6data3_train))
